WHAT would you do if your employer paid your salary many times over by mistake? Well, an office worker is on the run after his employer accidentally paid him 330 times his salary, making him an instant millionaire. According to Daily Mail, the unnamed man from Chile disappeared after promising to send the money back. It was reported that the HR employee at Chilean frozen foods giant Cial received £150 000 (about R3 million) on 30 May. READ: Cyril's millions: President off the hook The man was reportedly expecting to get his monthly salary of £450 (about R9 000) when the shocking payment graced his account. “After telling his line manager what happened, he was advised to go to the bank the next morning to return the cash face to face. But the company claims he never turned up,” the article read. The whereabouts of the man are unknown, and the company is suing him in attempts to reclaim the money. It is reported that the employee has submitted his resignation through a lawyer.